column5: seen a couple adventurous people out in there boats today, guess trying to get a last walleye meal, nice day around 9 here decided to do a little work on the sled, 10 years old this fall and still cant get enough of it.
and a very fitting sticker too... HAHAHAHA!

Nice ride! I just pulled the old 500 trail deluxe out for a once over and a tsk tsk at the remaining mickey mouse setups leftover from the mystery fire last winter. Cant wait to get out on the ice now.. After another day or 2 of muskie fishing of course
Oh ya, pays to take care of your kit. Nice looking machine.
Yah Geoff... sticker was the first thing that caught my eye!! Nice ride Ernie!  Reminds me, I have to get my 1998 out and see what's clicking in the track system, but lots of fishing to do first!

Hey wayne, my buddies enticer had a click when we pulled it out of storage, turned out a screw popped out the back of the slider so we drilled it out and slammed a new screw in and problem solved. Maybe an easy place to start lookin.
Very clean machine, but it definitely needs a turbo!
